title: Proton photoproduction from 12C.

x4codes.hlp: Univ. of Glasgow, Glasgow, Scotland, United Kingdom

x4freetext: The photon energy resolution was ~ 2 MeV and the total
photon flux,  over the 114 to 792 MeV  tagged  photon
thin AE  layers  followed  by  four  thick  E-layers.
Associated  particles were detected in TOF,  an array
of plastic scintillator time-of-flight  detectors  of
dimensions 200 x 50 x 3000 mm long mounted vertically
Data from Figs.  2 - 11 were compiled  at  the
Russia MSU SINP CDFE by V.Varlamov.
